00:08:30.660 --> 00:08:38.639
I cried, literally I cried every day that I had to go to work.

00:08:38.639 --> 00:08:51.639
Not only was I overwhelmed being a new nurse, but also I was battling my depression.

00:08:51.639 --> 00:08:57.720
In 2017, I was the treasurer for a prestigious bank in Nicaragua, and I was the father of

00:08:57.720 --> 00:08:59.519
a one-year-old son.

00:08:59.519 --> 00:09:06.700
We were very happy, but then I lost my job.

00:09:06.700 --> 00:09:13.259
So I said, I have the experience, and Jehovah will help me find another job.

00:09:13.259 --> 00:09:17.779
He's similar, and I kept looking for jobs, but doors kept closing.

00:09:17.779 --> 00:09:28.539
I felt very tense, it made me feel very useless, like I can't even provide for my family.

00:09:28.539 --> 00:09:38.620
It was something very difficult for me.

