For the things seen are temporary, but the things unseen are everlasting.

00:50:36.000 --> 00:50:39.199
Do you see why we can't give up?

00:50:39.199 --> 00:50:44.800
It's because being one of Jehovah's Witnesses requires that we remain active and persevere

00:50:44.800 --> 00:50:48.039
in the way of peace.

00:50:48.039 --> 00:50:52.840
You dear candidates have not given up in your efforts to please Jehovah and to qualify

00:50:52.840 --> 00:50:55.039
to become part of His people.

00:50:55.039 --> 00:50:58.639
And why is that?

00:50:58.639 --> 00:51:01.079
It's because of your love for Him.

00:51:01.079 --> 00:51:08.559
And you know that any trials and obstacles you face now are momentary and light when

00:51:08.559 --> 00:51:13.519
compared to an eternity in God's new world.

00:51:13.519 --> 00:51:18.599
Today you will enter into a special relationship with Jehovah God.

00:51:18.599 --> 00:51:25.360
So don't let anyone or anything jeopardize that relationship.

00:51:25.360 --> 00:51:33.719
Let it be something that you cherish because that relationship is everlasting.

00:51:33.719 --> 00:51:38.079
So keep walking in Jehovah's way of peace.

00:51:38.079 --> 00:51:44.760
Notice on what it means to have Him as a friend, to have Him guiding your steps.

00:51:44.760 --> 00:51:52.639
If you don't give up, then despite any trials you face, you will continue to enjoy Jehovah's

00:51:52.639 --> 00:51:54.679
blessings.

00:51:54.679 --> 00:51:58.360
And we're confident that you can do so.

00:51:58.360 --> 00:52:04.639
But to highlight how this can be done, at this time, we're pleased to introduce Sister

00:52:04.679 --> 00:52:07.159
Indira Alfonso.

00:52:07.159 --> 00:52:13.239
Sister Alfonso was baptized in 2006, and now serves with her husband as Bethel family members

00:52:13.239 --> 00:52:15.840
in Warwick.

00:52:15.840 --> 00:52:22.199
Sister Alfonso, can you tell us a little about your journey, how you became associated with

00:52:22.199 --> 00:52:23.199
Jehovah's Witnesses?

00:52:23.199 --> 00:52:28.639
Yes, I was born in Cuba, but my mom and I moved to the United States when I was nine.

00:52:28.639 --> 00:52:31.840
Even though I was young, I felt it was important to look for God.

00:52:31.840 --> 00:52:36.480
So whenever we moved, I would visit the local churches in the area, even getting baptised

00:52:36.480 --> 00:52:37.960
in a number of them.

00:52:37.960 --> 00:52:43.679
When I was 11, my mom let me move in with my aunt, who was one of Jehovah's Witnesses.

00:52:43.679 --> 00:52:48.719
And from there, she asked my mom if I could study with a pioneer sister from her congregation

00:52:48.719 --> 00:52:50.039
and my mom agreed.

00:52:50.039 --> 00:52:55.199
Well, nice to see that even at a young age, you had a spiritual need.

00:52:55.199 --> 00:53:01.159
So during this time leading up to your baptism as one of Jehovah's Witnesses, did you encounter

00:53:01.159 --> 00:53:03.880
any trials that threatened to make you give up?

00:53:03.880 --> 00:53:05.360
Yes, I did.

00:53:05.360 --> 00:53:06.920
I made changes very quickly.

00:53:06.920 --> 00:53:12.119
I stopped celebrating holidays, stopped praying to idols, but these changes were very

00:53:12.119 --> 00:53:16.559
strange to my mom, just difficult for her to understand.

00:53:16.559 --> 00:53:19.320
She really was afraid I was being brainwashed.

00:53:19.320 --> 00:53:24.159
So after studying for several months, she had me moved back in with her, which meant the

00:53:24.159 --> 00:53:27.840
end of my studies and no more attending meetings.

00:53:27.840 --> 00:53:32.960
It wasn't long before my association was affecting my speech and my behavior.

00:53:32.960 --> 00:53:37.239
I found myself easily influenced to even celebrate my birthday again.

00:53:37.239 --> 00:53:41.440
I could feel I was moving further away from Jehovah instead of closer to him.

00:53:41.440 --> 00:53:44.639
I'm sorry to hear that sister, Alfonso.

00:53:44.639 --> 00:53:49.880
So what helped you not to give up and to go on walking in the way of peace?

00:53:49.880 --> 00:53:54.800
What helped me was this scripture in Matthew 1037, where Jesus said, whoever has greater

00:53:54.800 --> 00:53:59.440
affection for father or mother than for me is not worthy of me.

00:53:59.440 --> 00:54:04.320
I realized that a peaceful relationship with Jehovah might mean no peace with my family.

00:54:04.320 --> 00:54:08.880
But I knew that if I were to ever gain my mom, I had to walk with Jehovah the right way

00:54:08.880 --> 00:54:10.599
and not give up.

00:54:10.599 --> 00:54:15.440
So one night I prayed to him, crying for forgiveness and asking for his help.

00:54:15.440 --> 00:54:20.360
Until my surprise a few days later, without any explanation, my mom had me moved back in

00:54:20.360 --> 00:54:21.760
with my aunt.

00:54:21.760 --> 00:54:27.840
I resumed my Bible studies and after a year later at the age of 15, I got baptized.

00:54:27.840 --> 00:54:32.000
Jehovah clearly heard and answered your prayer.

00:54:32.000 --> 00:54:36.239
Since then, have you seen continued evidence of Jehovah's guidance?

00:54:36.239 --> 00:54:40.719
A good friend helped me to adjust the way I was communicating with my mom.

00:54:40.719 --> 00:54:45.280
So one day I called her and expressed to her, how much I truly appreciate and love her.

00:54:45.280 --> 00:54:48.320
I didn't want us to be distant anymore.

00:54:48.400 --> 00:54:55.280
I explained to her that my love for her had never changed, but my love for Jehovah had come first.

00:54:55.280 --> 00:54:58.320
So that conversation was a turning point for us.

00:54:58.320 --> 00:55:03.599
Now we have had many positive discussions and she's much more understanding of my decision.

00:55:03.599 --> 00:55:09.519
Seeing Jehovah's guidance in my life makes me determined to continue walking in his way of peace.

00:55:09.519 --> 00:55:11.679
Thank you so much, Sister Alfonso.

00:55:11.679 --> 00:55:18.039
We appreciate your faithful example and comments.

00:55:18.039 --> 00:55:21.159
Well, let's address our second point.

00:55:21.159 --> 00:55:26.199
How did walking in Jehovah's way bring us peace?

00:55:26.199 --> 00:55:32.840
As to answer this, we're going to compare the path or journey you've taken on the road to life

00:55:32.840 --> 00:55:36.199
with a literal road or walkway.

00:55:36.199 --> 00:55:41.000
And in making this comparison, we find a number of similarities.

00:55:41.000 --> 00:55:48.760
First, both roads have boundaries, a purpose, and a destination.

00:55:50.519 --> 00:55:52.840
Let's start with that first one, boundaries.

00:55:54.039 --> 00:56:01.559
On a literal road, we may see yield or do not interest signs, guard rails on the side of the road,

00:56:02.199 --> 00:56:05.079
or lines on the road to help us stay in our lane.

00:56:06.360 --> 00:56:07.639
Well, those are boundaries.

00:56:08.440 --> 00:56:11.400
And those boundaries are there for our protection.

00:56:12.199 --> 00:56:17.639
Because if we step outside of them, we risk getting hurt or lost.

00:56:20.170 --> 00:56:25.769
It would be great if we could tell you that as you continue on the road to life after your baptism,

00:56:26.889 --> 00:56:30.730
we would love to say that the rest of your journey is smooth sailing.

00:56:30.730 --> 00:56:32.489
You'll have nothing but safe travels.

00:56:35.050 --> 00:56:41.289
But the reality is that you will face challenges and test of your faith.

00:56:43.050 --> 00:56:44.329
The devil will make sure of it.

00:56:46.010 --> 00:56:49.690
He will make sure that you are confronted with temptations.

00:56:51.050 --> 00:56:55.929
He wants to do whatever he can to damage your special relationship with Jehovah.

00:56:58.010 --> 00:57:00.090
But we're confident that you can succeed.

00:57:01.050 --> 00:57:09.210
You can be successful and avoid danger if you remain within the boundaries of Jehovah's way of peace.

00:57:11.050 --> 00:57:12.889
Now, how do you stay within those boundaries?

00:57:14.250 --> 00:57:19.929
By continuing to learn about Jehovah's laws and principles and obeying them.

00:57:21.769 --> 00:57:27.289
That obedience will not only protect you, but it will give you inner peace,

00:57:28.250 --> 00:57:31.210
peace that comes from having a clean conscience.

00:57:33.789 --> 00:57:38.829
The next similarity between a literal road and being on the road to life that we'll discuss

00:57:39.789 --> 00:57:41.630
is having a purpose.

00:57:43.309 --> 00:57:49.630
When we travel on a literal road, our plan usually is not to get on the road and just

00:57:50.190 --> 00:57:56.110
stand still, to become stationary or watch other people or vehicles go by.

00:57:56.510 --> 00:57:58.989
No, we're there for a reason.

00:57:59.949 --> 00:58:06.110
The purpose of the road is to enable movement to help us get from one place to another.

00:58:07.630 --> 00:58:14.590
Well, in a similar sense, being on Jehovah's way of peace allows you to move forward

00:58:15.469 --> 00:58:17.949
to make continual spiritual progress.

00:58:19.550 --> 00:58:23.150
And of course, there are many ways that we can make spiritual advancement.

00:58:24.110 --> 00:58:31.150
One important way that all Christians can do so is in cultivating spiritual qualities.

00:58:32.349 --> 00:58:34.190
This is so pleasing to Jehovah.

00:58:35.309 --> 00:58:39.309
Consider with me, for example, Galatians chapter 6, verse 10.

00:58:43.900 --> 00:58:49.559
Notice what's mentioned here, Galatians chapter 6, verse 10.

00:58:50.840 --> 00:58:57.800
It says, so then, as long as we have the opportunity, let us work what is good toward all.

00:58:58.679 --> 00:59:03.239
But especially toward those related to us in the faith.

00:59:05.000 --> 00:59:11.400
So one way to advance spiritually is to look for ways to do good things for others,

00:59:12.039 --> 00:59:15.639
both inside and outside the congregation.

00:59:17.320 --> 00:59:20.599
This pandemic has afforded us many opportunities to do this.

00:59:21.880 --> 00:59:26.360
We've been able to call and check on others and distribute food or supplies when needed.

00:59:27.320 --> 00:59:33.719
And think of what our brothers have done time and again to assist others during natural disasters.

00:59:35.400 --> 00:59:38.440
So take a minute and think about your local area.

00:59:39.960 --> 00:59:43.079
How can you work what is good toward all?

00:59:45.239 --> 00:59:49.079
Are there ones that need assistance getting food or running errands?

00:59:50.599 --> 00:59:55.719
Is there someone who could use a good word of encouragement to cheer them up?

00:59:57.760 --> 01:00:00.559
Do we know individuals who have lost loved ones in death

01:00:01.360 --> 01:00:07.039
with whom we could share words of comfort or maybe simply provide a listening ear?

01:00:08.559 --> 01:00:12.159
You see, by displaying spiritual qualities,

01:00:12.159 --> 01:00:17.280
qualities such as kindness, compassion, hospitality, generosity,

01:00:17.920 --> 01:00:22.559
see, you're going to feel deeply rewarded for doing these things.

01:00:23.119 --> 01:00:30.960
And you're pleasing Jehovah because you will show that your purpose for being on the road to life

01:00:31.760 --> 01:00:36.480
is not just to save yourself, but to help others.

01:00:39.199 --> 01:00:44.079
And there was a third similarity between being on a literal road and being on the road to life.

01:00:45.280 --> 01:00:50.960
In both cases, we have a destination that we want to reach.

01:00:51.360 --> 01:00:56.480
Traveling on a literal path will eventually take you to your destination.

01:00:56.480 --> 01:01:02.559
And as a witness of Jehovah, our journey, our walk on this figurative road,

01:01:02.559 --> 01:01:11.679
will lead us to our destination, the goal of enjoying a peaceful friendship with God forever.

01:01:11.679 --> 01:01:20.039
Now, although we long for that time in God's new world, even now we can experience the blessings

01:01:20.599 --> 01:01:25.239
and inner peace that come from a life of service to Jehovah.

01:01:27.820 --> 01:01:30.699
We now have the privilege to speak with Sister Gloria Hurd.

01:01:31.900 --> 01:01:38.059
Sister Hurd has been baptized for over 70 years and has enjoyed a rich spiritual life

01:01:38.059 --> 01:01:43.179
and special full-time service with her husband, brother Samuel Hurd, of the governing body.

01:01:45.179 --> 01:01:51.739
Sister Hurd, you've had many rich spiritual blessings and we know that you've encountered

01:01:51.739 --> 01:01:57.500
challenges along the way. But as you've carried out these assignments through the years,

01:01:58.219 --> 01:02:04.059
walking in Jehovah's way of peace, how have you managed to enjoy greater inner peace?

01:02:05.019 --> 01:02:08.059
I learned, Brother Turner, that if Jehovah gives you an assignment,

01:02:08.619 --> 01:02:14.219
he will give you what you need to fulfill it. We learned and really benefited from the

01:02:14.219 --> 01:02:18.860
traveling overseas and their wives. It was such a privilege to serve along with these faithful

01:02:18.940 --> 01:02:23.820
brothers and sisters and several of them had served me and my family when I was very young.

01:02:24.539 --> 01:02:30.699
So to see their faithfulness, to see their happiness and to see that they really had inner peace,

01:02:31.659 --> 01:02:36.860
really benefited me. I learned from that and I wanted to follow their example.

01:02:36.860 --> 01:02:41.260
That help from others can be so valuable. How else have you managed?

01:02:41.820 --> 01:02:48.460
I've enjoyed inner peace too from praying to Jehovah a lot. Many times we had very little

01:02:48.460 --> 01:02:54.380
money or no money, but we never missed a meal and we never missed any theocratic event.

01:02:55.260 --> 01:03:02.219
We learned that having no money is not an obstacle to Jehovah. He heard our prayers,

01:03:02.219 --> 01:03:07.500
he answered them and it was if the blessing sometime just fell out of heaven.

01:03:08.139 --> 01:03:11.179
Prayer can be so powerful. Thank you for sharing that.

01:03:12.300 --> 01:03:17.340
But now, how has walking in Jehovah's way of peace helped you to have peace with others?

01:03:18.059 --> 01:03:23.340
I worked and lived with many sisters and they all had different personalities.

01:03:23.980 --> 01:03:29.980
So I learned that I had to apply Romans 12, 18 where it says, as far as it depends upon me,

01:03:31.500 --> 01:03:39.579
be peaceable with all men and women. So I learned that I have to adjust my personality sometimes to

01:03:39.659 --> 01:03:49.019
keep peace. This happened very often, but one time we moved in with a sister on Tuesday morning

01:03:49.739 --> 01:03:57.739
and something I said upset her very much. She got very angry. Well, I decided not to pursue the

01:03:57.739 --> 01:04:04.940
issue because I had lived with her for a week and I just decided to let her see by my conduct

01:04:05.019 --> 01:04:11.179
that I could never have met what she thought. So as the week went by, the days went by, the tension

01:04:11.179 --> 01:04:18.539
lesson and by Monday, when we left, we were the best of friends and she gave me a big hug

01:04:18.539 --> 01:04:22.460
and nothing more was said about the subject. Well, it sounds like you handled that beautifully

01:04:22.460 --> 01:04:29.099
sisterhood. Your spiritual qualities were evident. Well, finally, how has walking in Jehovah's

01:04:29.099 --> 01:04:35.900
way of peace helped you have peace with God? Well, when you see Jehovah acting your behalf over

01:04:35.900 --> 01:04:42.139
and over and over again, it makes you feel that you have his approval. Now that Sam and I are in

01:04:42.139 --> 01:04:47.659
our senior years, we feel he has given us the desire of our heart by allowing us to serve

01:04:47.659 --> 01:04:53.900
at Bethel, which had been our goal for many years. And I know that as long as I stay faithful to

01:04:53.900 --> 01:05:00.860
Jehovah, he will continue to grant me inner peace. And we have that confidence as well.

01:05:00.860 --> 01:05:07.179
Thank you so much, sisterhood. We deeply appreciate your comments and your encouraging expressions.

01:05:10.599 --> 01:05:17.880
Well, let's now address our final point. What can we do to continue walking in Jehovah's

01:05:17.880 --> 01:05:24.760
way of peace? Well, let's go back to our illustration of the road. On a literal road,

01:05:24.760 --> 01:05:30.760
travelers may need to make adjustments in response to changing road conditions or bad weather.

01:05:32.199 --> 01:05:39.159
Similarly, as you go on walking in the way of peace, you will need to readjust your actions

01:05:39.159 --> 01:05:46.360
and thinking from time to time. Recently, a circuit overseer shared an interesting point regarding

01:05:46.360 --> 01:05:52.360
our thoughts and attitudes on matters. He said that they could either serve as a prison

01:05:52.760 --> 01:06:01.639
or a passport. A prison in that our thoughts and actions can confine or restrict us

01:06:03.320 --> 01:06:13.280
or a passport in that they can take us where we need to be. Right now, we need to be

01:06:14.079 --> 01:06:22.239
and stay on this road to life. So we want to make sure that any needed adjustments are made in

01:06:22.239 --> 01:06:30.000
our thoughts and our actions so that we're not confined or restricted in making spiritual progress.

01:06:32.159 --> 01:06:39.039
Well, what might be some areas that we'll need to make adjustments? Notice, please, Paul's words

01:06:39.039 --> 01:06:48.909
in 2nd Corinthians chapter 13. And we'll read 2nd Corinthians chapter 13 verse 11.

01:06:56.300 --> 01:07:03.420
Paul says, finally, brothers, continue to rejoice, to be readjusted, to be comforted,

01:07:04.219 --> 01:07:11.980
to think in agreement, to live peaceably, and the God of love and of peace will be with you.

01:07:14.239 --> 01:07:19.119
Did you notice three areas in this verse where Paul states we can make adjustments?

01:07:20.079 --> 01:07:30.239
First, he says, continue to rejoice. We can lose our peace and joy if we become overwhelmed by

01:07:30.239 --> 01:07:38.559
the anxieties of life. So in order to rejoice, can you make it a goal to focus on things that

01:07:38.559 --> 01:07:46.159
bring joy rather than sadness? So if you're not feeling well or coping with chronic pain,

01:07:47.119 --> 01:07:56.320
you can focus on God's promise when no one will say, I am sick. If you're facing beliefs or

01:07:56.320 --> 01:08:02.960
or opposition for your beliefs, focus on the fact that we're part of a brotherhood, a brotherhood

01:08:02.960 --> 01:08:09.199
that supports and prays for us, and arrangements are in place to keep us spiritually strong.

01:08:11.530 --> 01:08:17.930
If you're discouraged by world events, you can rejoice in the fact that you have a hope for

01:08:18.010 --> 01:08:25.369
the future. And we know how this all ends. We know that better times are ahead.

01:08:27.130 --> 01:08:35.130
The point is, don't let negative thoughts restrict or limit your progress. Instead,

01:08:36.010 --> 01:08:41.369
make the needed adjustments so that you can move forward and continue to rejoice.

01:08:43.689 --> 01:08:47.050
Not another area for readjustment, Paul mentions in verse 11.

01:08:48.090 --> 01:08:56.140
There he says, continue to think in agreement. There were members of the congregation back in

01:08:56.140 --> 01:09:03.979
the first century that were promoting apostate ideas. Others were introducing controversial ideas

01:09:03.979 --> 01:09:11.739
that were not directly unscriptural, but that were divisive. This resulted in bickering and

01:09:11.739 --> 01:09:16.939
arguing, arguments over words, really creating a spiritually unhealthy atmosphere.

01:09:18.859 --> 01:09:22.699
Well, what's going to help us to continue to think in agreement?

01:09:24.619 --> 01:09:31.739
Remember Paul's words at 2nd Timothy 2, 23, to reject foolish and ignorant debates

01:09:32.779 --> 01:09:40.300
knowing that they produce fights. Of course, we react strongly when facing issues that

01:09:40.300 --> 01:09:47.100
clearly violate Jehovah's moral laws. But if no scriptural principle is being violated,

01:09:48.539 --> 01:09:52.140
we're wise to abstain from promoting our personal opinions.

01:09:53.500 --> 01:10:01.180
We want to do all we can to avoid starting or being drawn into disagreements that can disrupt

01:10:01.180 --> 01:10:10.060
the peace of the congregation. Now back in verse 11, a third area where we can make adjustments

01:10:10.779 --> 01:10:19.039
is continue to live peaceably. Did you notice from the interview with our sisters

01:10:20.000 --> 01:10:26.000
what they both did when challenged, would face with the challenge that threatened their peace?

01:10:27.680 --> 01:10:33.920
They took the matter to Jehovah in prayer. They reflected on scriptures found in God's word.

01:10:34.560 --> 01:10:39.680
And then they looked to see how they could apply those verses in their particular situation.

01:10:40.640 --> 01:10:46.560
It helped them to not only have inner peace, but peace with others as well.

01:10:48.159 --> 01:10:55.039
So let your spiritual qualities shine through. Continue to work on keeping peace,

01:10:55.039 --> 01:10:58.560
showing those qualities of being loving and generous toward all.

01:10:59.920 --> 01:11:05.279
But especially with our close family members, whether they are witnesses or not.

01:11:08.079 --> 01:11:13.760
Well, we want to conclude by reminding you baptism candidates that today marks a significant

01:11:13.760 --> 01:11:22.239
milestone in your journey, in your relationship with Jehovah. So take the time to appreciate

01:11:22.880 --> 01:11:31.920
what this day means for you. We're so proud of all of you. You will never regret the decision

01:11:32.000 --> 01:11:40.560
you have made to dedicate your life to Jehovah. But keep in mind that after today and beyond,

01:11:41.920 --> 01:11:49.600
the journey is not yet over. Really it's just the beginning. So we encourage you to do all you can

01:11:50.319 --> 01:11:58.640
to stay on the road to life. Keep in mind the points we consider today. First, do not give up on

01:11:58.640 --> 01:12:05.920
walking in Jehovah's way of peace. Your life depends on it. Allow Jehovah to guide your steps.

01:12:07.520 --> 01:12:14.880
Second, stay within the boundaries on the road to life. Remember, you're walking with a purpose.

01:12:15.600 --> 01:12:22.159
And that will lead you to your destination. Peaceful friendship with Jehovah forever.

01:12:22.880 --> 01:12:31.520
And finally, keep making any needed adjustments in your thoughts, your attitude and actions so that

01:12:31.520 --> 01:12:38.399
you can maintain peace with Jehovah and peace with others. If you continue to do these things,

01:12:39.039 --> 01:12:45.279
not only will you have peace, but as the last part of 2 Corinthians 13 11 says,

01:12:46.239 --> 01:12:54.640
the God of love and of peace will be with you. May you always remember that promise,

01:12:54.640 --> 01:12:59.920
which Jehovah makes to those who go on walking in the way of peace.

01:13:02.239 --> 01:13:09.960
Thank you, brother Turner. Similar to last year, the arrangements for baptism will vary in each

01:13:09.960 --> 01:13:16.840
location. Each local congregation's elders have made suitable provisions in accord with local

01:13:16.840 --> 01:13:25.579
circumstances for candidates to be baptized after the conclusion of this session. We thank

01:13:25.579 --> 01:13:30.380
Jehovah for the timely spiritual food we enjoy during this session of the convention.

01:13:31.579 --> 01:13:35.899
Our next session will show us how to avoid common pitfalls to pursuing peace.

01:13:37.020 --> 01:13:40.699
It will highlight specific activities that peacemakers excel at.

